summary: Hi again :) I don't know if u got to see these pics - farfarawaysite(.)com/section/killingeve/gallery2/gallery1/gallery(.)htm -...
question: Hi again :) I don't know if u got to see these pics - farfarawaysite(.)com/section/killingeve/gallery2/gallery1/gallery(.)htm - there are pics from several eps of season two. Previously I thought that Villanelle was going to stab Niko, in the kitchen knife scene, but the pics show that he's okay and back with Eve! Do you think Villanelle is going to kill him, or hurt him to get to Eve at some point, or will she be more subtle this time around? More romantic even? I'd love to hear your thoughts!
answer:
Yeah I did see them!

Not gonna lie, right after we got the first trailer that showed the kitchen scene, I was worried that Villanelle was going to stab Niko too, mainly because the guy talking to her sounds a lot like him. But after seeing the promo photos and doing some thinking, I no longer think that. And I don’t believe it’s actually Niko she’s talking to during that scene anymore either. (Based on the episode descriptions we’ve gotten, I’m guessing whoever Villanelle is talking to is a new character she convinces to take her in while she heals from her stab wound.)

I think Niko is pretty irrelevant to Villanelle tbh. I don’t think the idea of hurting or killing him has or will ever cross her mind because she knows that he doesn’t really have Eve’s attention at the end of the day. Eve actively risked her marriage in S1 in favor of chasing Villanelle and I think Villanelle knows this. And after Villanelle finds out that Eve is tracking a new assasin, that’s no doubt where most of her jealously is going to be directed at. The new assasin is way more at risk of being killed by Villanelle than Niko is. (And I REALLY hope I’m right about this. Villanelle killing Niko would just be another Bill repeat. I do not want it to happen lol).

I also don’t think Villanelle will be seeking revenge on Eve for stabbing her. At least, that won’t be her main motivation. I could see her doing something more minor in order to get revenge. (That’s what I think that lipstick scene is. Villanelle is gonna send Eve a lipstick tube with a blade in it and that’ll probably be when her need for revenge ends). Jodie Comer has said that Villanelle’s reaction to the stabbing won’t be what people expect and most of the general audience probably expects Villanelle to be filled with rage and have a thirst for revenge. Instead, based on everything we know, I think we’re gonna get a Villanelle who is even more into Eve than she was before and will be pining for her.

summary: I’ve had Not Over You by Tessa Violet stuck in my head for like an hour. And I’m realizing it could be hilariously perfect for...
body:
I’ve had Not Over You by Tessa Violet stuck in my head for like an hour. And I’m realizing it could be hilariously perfect for Villaneve. It sounds so cute and bouncy, but quickly starts to sound just obsessive enough to fit them and I can’t get this out of my head.

“-and I keep asking how
I don’t know better by now
You try but you can’t shake me,
I think we’re going crazy,
Keep saying that we’re through but,
Baby I’m not over you
We’re quick to go attack
But when we split I need you back and
I tell myself we’re though but
Baby I’m not over you.”
